Obese child's diet: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Third of children between 9 and 13 are overweight, while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, and 5% are obese.
As recent research shows, obese children usually come from unhealthy families.
Again, we can see the importance of the environment and models around a human being for his or her health development.
Examples of such foods are usually sausages, which occur up to half more frequently in the families of children with normal weight.
19% of obese children had fried chips for dinner the day before the research connected to the education event Obesity is No Accident.
Moreover, obese children do not practice sports. However, only 15% of current schoolchildren reported that their parents have time for sports activities at least once a week.
The research was performed among 900 children.
The research took place at the end of last year's school year, and it included almost 900 elementary school children from throughout Bohemia.
It was the second year of the Obesity is No Accident event, supported by both the General Insurance Company and Unilever.
The project has been joined by over 12 thousand school children from 4th to 8th grades.
Healthy diet and sufficient sports activities are key determining factors causing a dramatic increase in children who are either overweight or obese.
Examples are only half of those who asked have five meals a day, in the breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner pattern, one of the basic preconditions of correct diet.
No lunch and sausage in the evening
Scientists warn that even relative details are important for healthy development, such as regular family breakfast time.
In Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren's families have breakfast together.
In most families, everyone has breakfast separately.
The most interesting discovery was that in one tenth of households people do not have breakfast.
Breakfast is the core of proper daily diet.
A survey has revealed that fries are more common in families with obese children.
Most people - regardless of their weight - drink sweet soft drinks every day (70%).
Though over 40% of children do regularly play sports, the number drops to less than half - 15% - when they are given parents.
Create your own menu
The second part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compose their own menu based on the offered selection and their taste and opinion.
"Diet preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy diet."
Their favourite meals include large number of flour, meat, and sweet dishes.
However, the final report of the survey concludes.
As the main dish for lunch, pasta won very closely over poultry.
However, children showed little interest in legumes, fish, and vegetable lunches.
Health attitude
The survey also showed that children are willing to change their eating habits if they are given correct information.
Participants from the control group showed a significant change in their food preferences after the end of the Obesity is No Accident educational lecture.
This was quite significant, for example, in case of sweet soft drinks, where children would start to prefer plain water.
In addition, for main course children ate poultry and fish more often, limiting sweet and dumplings.
A Stylist Must Be a Good Psychologist, Professionals Claim
In the opening article on stylist training, I was a bit angry about the amount of information in the introductory lessons.
I had no idea what was coming.
Lectures by three experts from the field; dressing tips for difficult figures; and a seminar on how it works in practice.
More is yet to come.
The closer we get to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks are waiting.
The training is held every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really loaded with information.
This time, together with Alenka, the Director, (there is no single man in the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not in perfect symmetry.
Most women are not perfectly symmetrical.
One has short neck, one has a boyish figure without proper curves, and one is overweight.
A stylist must know how to optically soften wide shoulders, make the neck look longer or add the curves needed.
The advice was to accentuate the figure of women such as Jennifer Lopez, i.e. with bigger breasts and hips and narrow waist.
If the skirt or trousers do not fit, then at least one piece should be custom-made.
You will not regret the investment, as fitting clothing is a very expensive item.
In a custom-made skirt you will feel much better than in one that keeps shifting, rolling, sliding, etc.
Boyish figures can wear clothes with ruffling, applique, embroidery or shirring.
Given the abundance of such information and figure types, I am glad to have a whole week to sort it all out in my head.
Still I fear it is too much, with regard to the homework we received.
Each participant was given a celebrity to create two outfits for day and night.
We must consider their current appearance, their fashion style, and figure type.
I am to dress Miranda Kerr who you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaigns.
Inside I am very happy, as she is so much easier to dress than, say, Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently gained about a ton (please understand I am exaggerating).
We must cut the clothing out of magazines or find them on the Internet and print and graphically process them.
Moodboard, as it is called, then expresses our personal style and attitude to graphic depiction.
It is important to think about the graphic part of styling.
A stylist is not only dressing physical people, but also creating product pages in magazines (based on specific instructions, such as trendy handbags, jackets, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about.
Then it was not until Sunday.
A stylist needs general knowledge
Following Saturday’s lecture, filled with information on figure types, was a delightful event with three guests from the field.
Styling, Honza Pokorný; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer, Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion, and a stylist should be able to use this fact.
A good stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in different ways.
In this case, variability is key.
The trench coat may be worn in the standard way, over jeans and T-shirt, as a coat; but it may also be worn on naked body, with step-ins, as a dress.
Another option is rolling up the sleeves or collar, and the whole look changes completely.
Play with it, he stressed.
However, I appreciated the following advice the most: "For your work, you need to know the rules perfectly."
'Then you can start breaking them,' Jakub told us.
Here I finally understood why we drill all the definitions and rules of what to mix with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see something else.
Not mention fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that stylist must have more outfit versions than the number he is able to take pictures of.
Then, for a ten-page fashion story (equals ten outfits), I have to be ready to create at least fifteen of them.
Now I also know that in picture, a piece of clothing often looks and functions in combination with others completely different from reality.
The following is a further consideration when creating an outfit.
Honza Pokorný confirmed that image and style are half the success.
Madonna is no miraculous singer, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world-wide star.
The attitude to stylist services is still quite cold in Czech Republic.
Even famous people often consider it redundant (believing it is sufficient to be good at something, and how they look at it comes second).
If someone finally lets us create their styling, we should expect them to give us different (smaller) size than what they actually wear.
Then, we are left to Google and see if the tabloids wrote something about a celebrity gaining/losing weight, etc.
On Sunday, both Honza and Mario stressed that stylists are not enough to know fashion and be able to create an outfit.
Our work mainly consists of communicating with people we dress, so it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to estimate people, not to pander, and stick to one's opinion.
If a manager asks you to go through her clothes and add some nice pieces, you cannot throw out her whole wardrobe telling her how ugly the clothes are.
"Find at least a few pieces you can praise, and recommend what to wear them with" Mario says.
Then he showed us what specifically a duty bag must contain.
The bag you secure around your waist to carry all the props you need.
Beyond the usual things such as scissors, sticky roller, or safety pins, it should have nylon thread (for the stylist to use when taking pictures of products such as purses or hats), special clip-ons for holding the clothes in case it is too large (pins and similar things are forbidden), or a sewing set.
To have change from listening, and gain some practical experience, we learned how to properly underlay shoes.
Even when taking photographs in a studio where the surface is even, the soles may get damaged.
Because we kept away, we kept going.
You must not touch the shoes with scissors to prevent any damage.
This requires real skill.
Mario pleased me by congratulating my job.
The skills mentioned are not my cup of tea.
This is just a fragment of what we heard during the second weekend course session.
I am beginning to realize that being a professional stylist is no piece of cake, no matter what people say.
V Need for Speed: The Run takes place across America.
Review
The original carefree ride turned into a routine morning drive to work because of a series of completely unnecessary and sloppy mistakes.
The ambitions were achieved at some point, but it does not matter since nobody wanted to do any extra work.
The new version titled The Run was a highly anticipated release.
The game promises to change the old Need For Speed series in a new direction, and the demos made it look like a game that might stand up in the action racing genre.
The main character gets out of the car and runs.
The series ends with many different things than we expected.
The game represents a possibly decent arcade race, but the whole is burdened by several unnecessary mistakes that have been featured in the series for a number of years.
This means they are not mistakes, but the expression of an incomprehensible laziness of the developers.
The adventure starts well.
You are introduced to a story, where the main character, Jack, decides to solve some personal issues by participating in an illegal race across America.
The first person to get into the car is in San Francisco, and your task is to be the first one to reach New York.
The idea brings several interesting features.
The route is divided into ten stages, divided into over fifty races.
This means each race takes place on a different route, and given stages are set in different and interesting environments.
One therefore does not feel the game keeps offering the same things.
The graphics are very similar to previous parts of the series, but some of the environments are very nice to look at.
Still, it is not world-shattering.
driving through desert, autumnal countryside, or high in snow-covered mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the races are, occasionally, colored by an unusual feature.
Examples of desert areas are sandstorms, significantly reducing the visibility.
In contrast, in the mountains you must be careful not to get under an avalanche.
Individual races are ordered well.
There are only a few types, but it is sufficient.
Then you try to overtake a number of competitors (basic regular race); then you try to beat the time (standard stopwatch race); or you are in a duel with a single rival.
On top of everything else you sometimes get a few police officers who make your efforts more difficult.
The parts outside the car are new.
The animations are just interactive animations, where mostly Jack is running away from someone and you need to help him by pressing the right button at the right time.
No difficult.
The surprise is that the parts are much less than you would expect (just three to be precise).
It actually works for the game, because this feature does not get boring; within what was already said, it is one of the things that make the game more entertaining.
The driving model follows the footsteps of previous parts.
This means that it is no more special, but it cannot be considered a negative.
If you are looking for a real-to-life simulation, you will have to look elsewhere.
Still, this driving model is fully suitable for action style racing, even though we could find better at the competition.
So far everything is very good.
After some time problems appear.
In contrast with the driving model, the collision model is not that good.
The game is not expected to have complicated deformations and collisions, but when you have no idea before crashing into any object how your car will act, something is wrong.
When overtaking or passing cars tightly in common traffic you sometimes lightly touch the other car, but sometimes in nearly the same situation your car ends in wild pirouettes.
Or, completely crashed.
This is not such a big deal due to the restart system, but is enough to spoil the fun.
The restarts are done so that if you crash or get far off the track, the game takes you back to the last interrupted point.
The only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them up, you have to start the race from the start.
This makes it an aid in case something does not work, but you cannot rely on it completely.
sometimes the restarts are not enough and you need to learn a specific section of the race by heart.
The game’s main shortcoming is that the same things often happen in the same place.
Examples of some turns have to be driven through in a specific way, otherwise you will not fit in.
Other times you meet civilians at a given place in the same configuration, no matter if you come first, fifth, five seconds later or one minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations where you can see your rival drive through the two cars so easily, while when you get there the cars are already positioned so you can either drive around or slow down.
It does not matter when you get to them; everything is set up so that the situation always occurs right in front of your nose.
The competitors have other advantages, too.
While playing the game you will find several places, where, regardless of time, the same competitor will replace you at the same spot.
The most noticeable sight is at the end of the game, on a long bridge, where you are driving in the opposite direction.
Obviously your rival has to get ahead no matter what.
The thing is that when he is driving in front of you, he makes your vision worse, which causes you to crash the car a few times in the section.
One can understand the effort to make the game more interesting and adrenalin-filled, but it is so obvious it gets annoying quickly.
It's a pity, because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes even so full of action you cannot focus on what is going on around you.
It is not important if you do not get bored is the concept with fifty unique tracks, ordering of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
The gas stations are often located along the way, as they are where your car may change despite the fact that most cases your current one is fully sufficient.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; strong American cars for straight highway sections; and exotic sports cars for technical driving such as along crooked mountain tracks.
The key story mode is closely connected with the challenge mode, and these are the races in individual locations you know from the story.
Here you gain both medals and experience points for your profile, common for both challenges and the story.
Various features are available for getting a higher driver level: starting with cars and ending with profile backgrounds.
Again, the profile is linked to an on-line Autolog function, which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players, and ensures community functions.
The next setback is the situation from the last race in the story.
You and your car get into a subway tunnel (let's say you do), where you speed down the tracks in darkness (let's say you do).
The speedometer shows numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (let's say it does), when suddenly a subway train rolls down from behind you, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
The editorial staff kept talking about whether when designing the game no one thought for a moment or whether its authors really think we are such morons.
The technical part of the game is nothing special, but the visual impression is mostly pleasant, sometimes even great.
The recording, in some cases, sometimes tragically, decreases.
This is particularly important in large numbers of participants, where fluent recoding would not help you much.
The sound is all right; the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
The soundtrack is 'flecked in from all quarters' but there will be no many people buying the game because of its music.
Overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confused.
If the game avoided those clearly redundant mistakes, The Run is the best part of NFS for the past several years.
However, the game feels unfinished.
It is surely a good entertainment, but be prepared to be blinded by the mistakes with the strength of airport spotlights.
UK Choirs will Sing at Students for Velvet Concert
The third year of the Festa Academia Festival is a celebration of international Students' Day and Velvet Revolution.
It will introduces about 20 high school and university choirs.
The main focus of the festival is on two concerts taking place on November 17.
Charles University has been involved in the festival.
Participants include the Pedagogical Department and Humanities Chorus; Václav Hampl, the Rector, will be in the Committee.
The climax will be a free public concert by high school choirs, which will take place at 2 p.m. on November 17, at the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
Celebration Jazz Mass, a piece by an important Czech jazzman, Karel Růžička is on the programme.
In the evening, in the ceremonial National House in Vinohrady, there will be a "Students for Velvet" concert, featuring university choirs, including those from Charles University.
The aim of Academica is to celebrate the International Students' Day and commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with dignity, as well as to present the public with top quality choir music, and to develop creative cooperation among young people.
The main organizing body is Czech Chorus in cooperation with Jan Kepler's Grammar School.
The event is under the supervision of Bohuslav Svoboda, Lord Mayor of Prague, and Václav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20, in Prague and Pardubice.
The programme includes both ceremonial concerts and numerous musical meetings, students' events, matinées and more.
Read more on the festival website at: www.academia.cz
